  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess the safety profile of brentuximab vedotin in
      combination with multi-agent chemotherapy in treatment-naive Stage IIa or IIb-IV Hodgkin
      lymphoma. It is a phase 1, two-arm, open-label dose escalation study designed to define the
      maximum tolerated dose, pharmacokinetics, immunogenicity and anti-tumor activity of
      brentuximab vedotin in combination with frontline therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
